'vernciph' - one-time pad (aka Vernam Cipher) implementation for *NIX-like OS.

Build:
    make install

Usage:
Encrypting
    vernciph -e -k /path/to/input/key/file < /path/to/input/file > /path/to/output/file
    vernciph -e < /path/to/input/file > /path/to/output/file 2> /path/to/key
Decrypting
    vernciph -d -k /path/to/key/file < /path/to/encrypted/file > /path/to/decrypted/file

If key file is not exists it will be created at specified path and data will be readed from /dev/random

